\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 201. C. rhaetica} Moritzi,{\i  Neue Denkschr. Schweiz. Ges. Naturw.}{\b  3}: 81 (1839) ({\i C. cirrhata} Reichenb. pro parte). Perennial. Stems 10-60 cm, numerous, erect or ascending, simple or sparingly branched. Leaves subcoriaceous, scabrid, otherwise glabrous, rarely subfloccose, undivided; lower oblong- to linear-lanceolate; upper semiamplexicaul; uppermost sometimes hastate, entire. Capitula solitary, sessile. Involucre 14-20 × 8-15 mm, ovoid-cylindrical; appendages triangular, not completely covering the linear bracts, black at the base, narrowly semilunate-decurrent, the apex 7 mm, filiform, subulate, recurved, blackish-brown, plumose-fimbriate, the lower fimbriae very short, approximate, black, the upper fimbriae up to 3 mm, brown. Florets pink-purple, the outer radiate. Achenes c. 3 mm, pale brown; pappus up to 1 mm. 2n = 22.{\i  Open woods and meadows; calcicole. • S. Alps, from} 9°{\i  to }10° 45' {\i E.} He It.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen.{\b  Psephellus} (Cass.) Schmalh. Perennial; stems erect. Lower leaves pinnatisect; middle leaves entire or dentate, not pinnatisect. Appendages not decurrent, pectinate-fimbriate, not spinose. Corolla 5-fid. Pappus present, caducous.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 202. C. leucophylla} Bieb.,{\i  Fl. Taur.-Cauc.}{\b  3}: 591(1819). Stems 10-30 cm, simple, ascending. Leaves whitish-green above, grey-tomentose beneath; lower pinnatisect, with obtuse segments; cauline lyrate. Involucre 8-15 mm in diameter; appendages triangular-lanceolate, yellow or pale brown. Florets pink, the marginal radiate.{\i  Steppes and rocky hillsides. Krym.} Rs (K). ({\i Caucasus}.)
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 203. C. declinata} Bieb., {\i op. cit.} 590 (1819). Like {\b 202} but involucre 15-20 mm in diameter; appendages brown.{\i  Rocky hillsides and coniferous woods. Krym.} Rs(K). ({\i Caucasus}.)
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 204. C. dealbata} Willd.,{\i  Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 2295 (1803). Stems up to 100 cm, branched, erect. Leaves green above, grey-tomentose beneath; lower pinnatisect, with acute segments, long-petiolate; upper surrounding the capitula, pinnatisect, rarely entire, sessile. Involucre 30-40 mm in diameter; appendages ovate-orbicular, yellowish-brown. Florets bright pink, the marginal distinctly patent.{\i  Cultivated for ornament and locally naturalized.} [Cz.] ({\i Caucasus}.)
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen.{\b  Heterolophus} (Cass.) Dobrocz. Like Subgen. {\i Psephellus} but stems usually procumbent; pappus persistent.
\par 

