\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 209. C. trinervia} Stephan ex Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 2301 (1803). Plant sparsely floccose-tomentose. Stems up to 30 cm, erect, leafless above. Leaves undivided, up to 70 × 4 mm, linear-lanceolate, distinctly 3-veined, entire, acute, the lower long-petiolate, the upper sessile. Involucre 6-10 × 12-15 mm; bracts pale green, with dark brown apex; middle bracts oblong-ovate. Florets pink, the outer longer than the inner, patent. Achenes 4-6 mm; pappus 2-3 mm. {\i Dry grassland. From C. Romania to S.E. Russia.} Rm Rs (W, K, E).
